In addition to these third-party integrations, we may share your data with various entities, including:
(1)Affiliated Entities: Other parts of HUMMINGBIRD GAMES PTE.LTD., which help us in developing and operating our Games and Services.
(2)Service Providers: External companies that provide services to us, such as hosting, analytics, or functionality enhancement, who process data on our behalf.
(3)Payment Processors: Companies handling transactions within our Games or Services, who may process your payment information independently.
(4)Business Partners: Collaborators involved in delivering and promoting our Services, including advertising partners.
(5)Business Transfers: Potential buyers or their representatives in the event of mergers, acquisitions, or restructuring.
(6)Legal Compliance: Courts or authorities if required by law or regulation.
(7)Legal Protection: To assert, establish, or defend legal rights or to protect the vital interests of you or others.
(8)With Your Consent: Any other individual or entity as permitted by your consent.
Be aware that some information you provide or make visible through our Services, such as your in-game alias or chat messages, may be accessible to other users.
VIII Data Retention
We will retain your data only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, including providing our Services and meeting any legal, accounting, or reporting obligations. Inactive accounts and data in our Games or Services may be periodically deleted or anonymized.
Once the retention period has elapsed, we will either delete or anonymize your data. If deletion or anonymization is not feasible (such as when data is stored on backup servers), we will isolate your data from further processing until such actions can be performed. We may continue to use data that cannot be traced back to you, such as aggregated data. We will not attempt to re-identify individuals when using such anonymized data.
IX Data Protection
We have implemented security measures designed to protect your data according to the risk level associated with the processing activities described in this Privacy Policy. These measures aim to prevent accidental or unlawful destruction, loss, alteration, unauthorized disclosure, or access to your data. The specific security practices we use can vary, but generally include encryption during transmission, pseudonymization of personal data when possible, access controls to restrict entry to systems containing personal data, and protocols for addressing suspected security incidents. Please be aware that while we strive to safeguard your data, the nature of the internet means we cannot guarantee complete security.
X Your rights
You have specific rights concerning your data in accordance with applicable laws and regulations. If we handle your data, you can exercise these rights. For example, you can request to access your data, ask for it to be deleted, or withdraw consent where applicable. To manage these rights, please use the options available in the settings of our Games or contact our Data Protection Officer (DPO). Your rights include:
(1)Accessing, correcting, or requesting the deletion of your data.
(2)Requesting restrictions on how we process your data.
(3)Objecting to our data processing based on legitimate interests.
(4)Requesting a machine-readable copy of the personal data you've provided to us, where feasible.
If our data processing is based on your consent, you can withdraw it at any time. To manage your advertising preferences, please contact our DPO. However, we may continue to process your data if we have legal reasons to do so, even if you withdraw your consent. For data access or deletion within our Games, use the provided options in the game settings or contact our DPO. If you have an account across our Games, you can also contact our DPO to request modifications or deletion of your account data. To exercise your rights, reach out to our DPO. We may need to verify your identity, which could involve requesting additional information. For inquiries related to payment methods or transactions, please contact the payment service provider directly.
XI Minor
Our Services are designed for a broad audience, including various age groups. While most of our offerings are suitable for all ages, some Games are intended for adults. If you choose to use these Games, you may be asked to confirm your age, or we may otherwise learn your age. If we determine that you are a minor or do not meet the age requirements, we may take necessary actions, such as restricting, suspending, or terminating your access to our Services. These measures are taken to comply with regulatory or platform requirements and to ensure a suitable user experience. If your access is not restricted or terminated, we will only use your personal data as needed for the operation of our Services and in compliance with relevant laws, regulations, and platform policies. This may involve limiting access to certain features or areas of the Services.
XII Updates
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or legal obligations. Any updates will be posted here, and we may also notify you through appropriate channels depending on the nature of the changes. Continued use of our Services will be considered as your acceptance of these changes.
